    Keynote Speaker

    Clement Boissiere 🇫🇷

    Founder of SXP Studio, Creative Technologist

    Clement focus on immersive digital experiences. With a background in Silicon Valley, he contributed to projects like Apple Vision Pro. Recently, he launched ShaderVision and the award-winning mixed reality game Pulsargeist.

    Cui Jonathan 🇨🇳

    Founder of TouchFuture, Head of XR Studio at TAL Group

    Jonathan Cui is the founder of TouchFuture, an XR game studio under TAL Education Group, with 10+ years of experience in roles such as programmer, planner, operator, and producer across PC, mobile, and XR games.

    Cheng Chen 🇨🇳

    Technical Operations Lead for the ModelScope Community

    ModelScope is an AI model community initiated by Alibaba, which has now become the largest AI model community in China. She was responsible for building the ModelScope community’s operational system from the ground up, as well as managing technical ecosystem integration.

    Cosmo 🇨🇳

    Founder of ILLUSION Tech, Creator of Seasons and Story

    Cosmo is the founder of ILLUSION Tech, which launched Seasons and Story, two hit apps recommended multiple times by Apple. Story is a platform for creating and sharing spatial content, while Seasons offers an immersive weather experience.

    Daiki Matsudate 🇯🇵

    Organizer of try! Swift Tokyo

    Daiki is a seasoned iOS developer with 14 years of experience, currently contributing to Digital Agency, gorvenment of Japan. He also supports the Japanese ride-sharing startup, Newmo, and serves as a technical advisor to various startups. As the main organizer of try! Swift Tokyo, Daiki plays a pivotal role in uniting the Swift developer community in Japan.

    Doug North Cook 🇺🇸

    App Store Awards 24 Winner, Creature CEO

    As CEO of Creature, Doug leads a studio focused on innovative design and technology. Under his leadership, Creature’s projects, including Starship Home and THRASHER, received top honors like Meta Quest's Top Mixed Reality Title and Apple’s Vision Pro Game of the Year.

    Allen Dang 🇨🇳

    AIGC Content Creator

    Head of Product Development, VAST | Founder of Photon Engine | Author of TripoGO! With 10 years of experience in interactive content product entrepreneurship, focusing on the integration of new technologies and content creation.

    Ming Dai 🇨🇳

    Senior iOS Developer

    Author of the Geek Time course "iOS Development Masterclass" and the book "Learn iOS Programming with Dai Ming," recently passionate about Apple Intelligence technologies.

    Eduardo Herranz 🇪🇸

    Co-founder Spatial Voyagers, XR ecosystem entrepreneur

    With over 10 years of experience, he has developed XR projects for brands like Disney, Ferrari, and Meta. Currently, he creates experiences for devices like Apple Vision Pro in entertainment and corporate communication. He also directs Spatial Computing programs at UCM and teaches at IE Business School.

    Terry Gao 🇨🇳

    Founder of Future East Label Spatial Audio Engineer

    The first Chinese artist at Liquid Sonics, Artistic Director for the Immersive Ethnic Music Album series in Dolby Atmos, and lead instructor for Creating Dolby Atmos Music with Logic Pro. He has also served as a judge for USC 2023’s Dolby Atmos Track.

    Giovanni Monaco 🇮🇹

    Senior Coding Mentor - imaginary institute

    As a Senior Mentor Coding at the Apple Developer Academy in Naples and a voice at Create with Swift, Giovanni empowers creators to develop impactful applications in the Apple ecosystem. He advocates for the synergy of technology and design, encouraging professionals to explore new frontiers in creativity.

    Hyacinth 🇨🇳

    AIGC Experimental Film Director

    Hyacinth is an experimental art director exploring the impact of AI on traditional film, animation, and game workflows. In 2024, Hyacinth produced the first AI animation for the Spring Festival Gala and won multiple awards, including Best Film at the 2024 Beijing International Film Festival’s AIGC section for To My Dear Me.

    Yang Xu 🇨🇳

    Fatbobman, Swift Blogger

    Blogger specializing in articles on SwiftUI, SwiftData, and Core Data.

    Jason Lee 🇺🇸 🇰🇷

    A technology mentor at Apple Developer Academy

    Jason Lee is a technology mentor at Apple Developer Academy South Korea, specializing in ML and guiding learners in using Apple frameworks.Previously, he facilitated Master’s courses at Boston University in data science and algorithms and contributed to genome assembly research at Harvard Medical School.

    Jie Ji 🇨🇳

    Creator of Chinese Character Repairer

    Concept Designer and Imagineer at Shanghai Disney. A 2018 National Scholarship recipient and 2021 Outstanding Graduate, Ji has won awards including the 3rd Disney Fantasy Engineering Challenge, Most Innovative Award at the China University Computer Competition, and the Red Dot and iF Design Awards.

    James Dale 🇦🇺

    the Founder of Friday Technologies

    an app developer and the founder of Friday Technologies, an app development studio that turns complex ideas into real-world apps. Previously, he worked on machine learning technologies at Apple and co-founded the US-based startup Have A Great Summer, backed by Google and BoxGroup (now acquired by Snapchat).

    Megabits 🇨🇳

    Indie Developer, PomoNow Creator

    Studied design in Japan. With nearly ten years of Swift development experience, his work spans multiple platforms, such as "PomoNow," "MagicPIP," "Fish Screen Reader," "Notch Simulator," and more. "PomoNow" has been featured on the App Store homepage several times.

    Mike Mandel 🇺🇸

    App Store Award 24 Winner, Co-Creator of THRASHER

    Mike Mandel is a game designer and creative technologist who co-founded Puddle and created THRASHER, Apple’s 2024 Vision Pro Game of the Year. With over a decade in XR, he has worked on projects like Rock Band VR and Fuser.

    Krishnaprasad Jagadish 🇮🇳

    Founder and CTO at Chaarana Labs

    Krishna is the Co-Founder and CTO of Chaarana Labs, a tech studio focused on creating immersive content for Apple Vision Pro. With over 15 years of experience in Apple platform development, his team’s app Immersive India has earned significant recognition and visibility on the platform.

    Simon Lee 🇨🇳

    AIGC Artist, 3D Artist

    Co-founder of AbleSlide, working with brands like Mercedes-Benz, BMW, ByteDance, and Alibaba. Blender artist for the French animated short 《 La Fontaine: Au cœur des Fables 》. AI artist behind 《 She Sleeps with Light 》 and 《 Dear Me 》. Weibo design influencer with over a million followers and a leading advocate for AI art in China.

    QianHui Liang 🇨🇳

    Founder of N7 Interactive, architect and interaction designer

    Liang, founder of N7 Interactive, is an architect and interaction designer passionate about connecting people, places, and scenes. Through its product, Sceno, N7 Interactive pioneers innovative ways to relive memories and share moments, redefining spatial storytelling and interaction.

    Wei Liu 🇨🇳

    Technical Director at Epic Games China

    He has nearly 10 years of experience in game development, has developed self-developed engine, has an understanding of all functional modules of engine, is good at rendering and efficiency optimization, and has been engaged in the development of terminal games, mobile games and apps.

    Keke Le 🇨🇳

    TAOBAO & TMALL GROUP Multi Platforms Innovation DesignDesign Leader

    Leading the design team to spearhead innovative cross-platform experience design projects, including Taobao for Vision Pro, the Tmall mobile app, and AI shopping assistants. These initiatives focus on experience design in mixed reality, artificial intelligence, and e-commerce.

    Linda Sheng 🇨🇳

    the GM of Global Business at MiniMax

    the GM, Global Business and Head of Investment at MiniMax. Prior to MiniMax, she was a technology investor at Warburg Pincus, a large US Private Equity fund. Before Warburg, Linda worked with Softbank Vision Fund in Silicon Valley and Asia, focusing on AI and technology investing.

    Peng 🇨🇳

    The Product Manager of Aqara

    Peng is a Product Manager of Aqara, responsible for defining and integrating Aqara products with third-party IoT platforms such as Matter and Apple Home. He has extensive experience in integrating products into various IoT platforms.

    Paul Hudson 🇬🇧

    Creator of Hacking with Swift

    Paul is the author of Hacking with Swift, Pro Swift, Swift Design Patterns, Testing Swift, Swift Interview Challenges, and more. Suffice it to say, he quite likes Swift. And coffee. (But mostly Swift.) (And coffee.)

    Ryan McLeod 🇺🇸

    Apple Design Awards 24 Winner Blackbox Creator
